				<img data-perfmatters-preload="" width="1200" height="675" src="https://i0.wp.com/eos.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ahr-river-germany-flooding-town.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-newspack-featured-image size-newspack-featured-image wp-post-image" alt="Aerial view of muddy-looking floodwaters from a meandering river flooding houses and buildings throughout a town spread on either side of the river" data-hero-candidate="1" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/eos.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ahr-river-germany-flooding-town.jpg?w=1200&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i0.wp.com/eos.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ahr-river-germany-flooding-town.jpg?resize=480%2C270&amp;ssl=1 480w, https://i0.wp.com/eos.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ahr-river-germany-flooding-town.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/eos.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ahr-river-germany-flooding-town.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/eos.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ahr-river-germany-flooding-town.jpg?resize=400%2C225&amp;ssl=1 400w, https://i0.wp.com/eos.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/ahr-river-germany-flooding-town.jpg?fit=1200%2C675&amp;ssl=1&amp;w=370 370w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px">			<figcaption><span>Floodwaters inundate a town along the Ahr River in Germany. Artificial intelligence, used skillfully and transparently, could aid disaster management efforts to mitigate the impacts of such events. Credit: Christian/Adobe Stock</span></figcaption>
			
